text: :The North African food is at couscous A Cuscus is a marsupial from Papua New Guinea. It has a pouch on its front where its baby begins to grow and develop in. The cuscus has thick white fur and a long tail, with a slightly pink tip. It uses its tail to help it climb through the trees. == References == Category:Marsupials of Australia Category:Papua New Guinea Category:Mammals of Oceania
